          "subtype": "message",
          "text": "## Summary\n\nI've successfully analyzed the project and updated the `package.json` to include all necessary dependencies. Here's what I found and fixed:\n\n### Analysis\nThe project uses the following external dependencies:\n1. **dotenv** - Used in both the test file (`tests/main.js`) and the config file (`config.js`) which are part of the published package\n2. **tap** - Test runner (already in devDependencies \u2713)\n3. **typescript** - For type checking (already in devDependencies \u2713)\n4. **@types/node** - Type definitions (already in devDependencies \u2713)\n5. **standard** - Code linting (already in devDependencies \u2713)\n6. **standard-version** - Release tool (already in devDependencies \u2713)\n\n### Changes Made\nAdded `dotenv` to the `dependencies` section in `package.json`:\n```json\n\"dependencies\": {\n  \"dotenv\": \"^17.0.0\"\n}\n```\n\n### Rationale\n- **dotenv** was missing but required by the project's `config.js` and test files\n- Version ^17.0.0 is compatible with Node 12+ (the project's minimum version)\n- Placed in `dependencies` rather than `devDependencies` because `config.js` is part of the package exports and needs dotenv to function\n\n### Verification\n\u2705 **All 97 tests passing**\n\u2705 **TypeScript type checking passes**\n\u2705 **No compilation errors**",
